      • beginToken

        boolean beginToken(Token token)
        Called if a new code point is available.
        Parameters:
        token - Used to return the token to the caller.
        Returns:
        true if the token continues (e.g. a string) or false if the token ended (i.e. it only consists of this single code point).

      • continueToken

        Lexer.TokenState continueToken(Token token)
                        throws CompilerError
        Called if a new code point is available and beginToken returned true and all previous calls for this token returned TokenState.Continues.
        Parameters:
        token - the current token.
        Returns:
        the state of the current token.
        Throws:
        CompilerError - compiler error

      • readToken

        void readToken(Token token)
        throws CompilerError
        Read exactly one token. This method calls nextChar() as necessary. On return, .codePoint() already returns the next code point for another call to beginToken(), if .continue_ is true.
        Parameters:
        token - used to return the token to the caller
        Throws:
